                  "body": "The area of a circle is the space occupied by the circle in a two-dimensional plane. It is proportional to the square of its radius."
                },
                {
                  "type": "formula",
                  "title": "Area Formula",
                  "equation": "A = \\pi r^2",
                  "equation_label": "A = Area, r = radius"
                },
                {
                  "type": "warning",
                  "body": "Do not confuse the radius with the diameter! The diameter is twice the radius ($d = 2r$). If given the diameter, divide by 2 first."
                },
